race.comment: THINK PINK DAZE (8) sat midfield but couldn't reel in the leader over 1200m at Ascot first-up in a stronger race than this, beaten 1.3L. Back to a CL1 today looks a good move and Pike remains with the filly second-up. Placed to advantage and can return to winning ways. ZIPPY ZANY (5) finished 5th last start but was only caught late, finishing 0.9L off the winner over 1500m at Ascot. Back in trip today, but Chris Parnham replaces the apprentice hoop and she's likely to be on the speed. Can make every post a winner. WINNING SHUFFLE (1) resumes from a long break but will be fitter for a couple of trials. Can feature. RAZMAS (6) trialled well in readiness for this and is not to be discounted.
